{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow all single-sex spaces to exclude people of the other biological sex",
        "additional_details": "I am a personal trainer and I am an advocate of women-only areas in gyms. Many women, such as those from certain faiths, don't wish to exercise before men. The Equality Act should be updated so that all woman-only spaces can exclude biological men.\r\n \r\nI believe that allowing transgender people into such areas can make women uncomfortable and can expose the transgender person to physical and verbal abuse. It's protection for both sides.",
        "background": "The Government should make it clear that all single-sex spaces can exclude people of the other biological sex without having to prove it is \"a proportionate means of achieving a legitimate aim\". There has been considerable social media coverage about biological men entering women-only spaces.",
